summary: An ordinance accepting a deed from Weyerhaeuser Timber Company, a corporation, duly incorporated under the laws of the State of Washington, to the City of Seattle, dated July 12, 1910, to certain tracts of land situated in section 27 and 23, Township 23 North, Range 8 East, W.M., in King County, State of Washington, and appropriating the sum of $328.20 from the general fund to pay for the purchase thereof.
